Package: kerneval
Type: Package
Title: Kernel density estimation with selection-biased data 
Version: 0.1.1.9000
Authors@R: person('Gawain', 'Antell', email='gawainantell@gmail.com', 
                  role=c('aut','cre'))
Depends: R (>= 4.0)
Description: The kerneval package implements tools for estimating and comparing probability density functions based on data that are biased by sampling (e.g. length-biased data). The statistical approaches could be used in many disciplines, although the package documentation focuses especially on applications to ecological analysis.
